# Basic of standard Module Structure
The standard odule structure is a file and directory layout HashiCorp recommends for reusable modules.

A minimal recommended module following the standard structure is shown below

# tree minimal module 
1. README.md
2. main.tf
3. variables.tf
4. outputs.tf

# Scope the requirements for Module creation
A team want to provision their infrastructure using terraform
The following architecture diagram depicts te desired outcome

# Planning a Module Structure
In this scenario, a team of Terraform producers, who write terraform code from scratch, will build a collection of modules to provision the infrastructure and applications.

# Final module output
After reviewing the consumer team's requirement, the producer team has broken up the application infrastructure into the following modules:

network web app db routing securty